description: Gets the details of services, for a tenant, that are onboarded to Azure Active Directory Connect Health.

notificationemailsenabledforglobaladmins.description: Indicates if email notification is enabled for global administrators of the tenant.

skip_count.description: The skip count, which specifies the number of elements that can be bypassed from a sequence and then return the remaining elements.

lastdisabled.description: The date and time, in UTC, when the service was last disabled.

notificationemailenabledforglobaladmins.description: Indicates if email notification is enabled for global administrators of the tenant.

monitoringconfigurationscomputed.description: The monitoring configuration of the service which determines what activities are monitored by Azure Active Directory Connect Health.

monitoringconfigurationscustomized.description: The customized monitoring configuration of the service which determines what activities are monitored by Azure Active Directory Connect Health.

disabled.description: Indicates if the service is disabled or not.

notificationemailenabled.description: Indicates if email notification is enabled or not.

notificationemails.description: The list of emails to whom service notifications will be sent.

additionalinformation.description: The additional information related to the service.

filter.description: The service property filter to apply.

service_type.description: The service type for the services onboarded to Azure Active Directory Connect Health. Depending on whether the service is monitoring, ADFS, Sync or ADDS roles, the service type can either be AdFederationService or AadSyncService or AdDomainService.

activealerts.description: The count of alerts that are currently active for the service.

customnotificationemails.description: The list of additional emails that are configured to receive notifications about the service.

displayname.description: The display name of the service.

simpleproperties.description: List of service specific configuration properties.

resolvedalerts.description: The total count of alerts that has been resolved for the service.

lastupdated.description: The date or time , in UTC, when the service properties were last updated.

tenantid.description: The id of the tenant to which the service is registered to.

take_count.description: The take count , which specifies the number of elements that can be returned from a sequence.

api_version.description: The version of the API to be used with the client request.

createddate.description: The date and time, in UTC, when the service was onboarded to Azure Active Directory Connect Health.

type.description: The service type for the services onboarded to Azure Active Directory Connect Health. Depending on whether the service is monitoring, ADFS, Sync or ADDS roles, the service type can either be AdFederationService or AadSyncService or AdDomainService.
